\begin_layout Standard
In the second dissection, the two scale factors are 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{\sqrt{5}}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{2}{\sqrt{5}}$
\end_inset

.
 Not coincidentally 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{5}}\right)^{2}+\left(\frac{2}{\sqrt{5}}\right)^{2}=1$
\end_inset

.
 In general, if 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathscr{C}=\{T_{1},T_{2},\ldots,T_{p}\}$
\end_inset

 is the set of similitudes that determine a rep-tile 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

, then
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
T_{1}(R)\cup T_{2}(R)\cup\cdots\cup T_{p}(R)=R
\]

\end_inset

and the images 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{k}(R)$
\end_inset

 pariwise have no overlapping area, so
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\text{area}\left(T_{1}(R)\right)+\text{area}\left(T_{2}(R)\right)+\cdots+\text{area}\left(T_{p}(R)\right)=\text{area}(R).\label{eq:reptile-area}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Now, we know from section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:Determinants-Eigenvalues-Area"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 that 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{area}\left(T_{k}(R)\right)=|\det L_{k}|\cdot\text{area}(R)$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{k}$
\end_inset

 is the matrix of the linear part of similitude 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{k}$
\end_inset

.
 We also know from section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:The-Inverse-Revisited"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 that the determinant of a product is the product of the determinants and
 from section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:The-Determinant-Revisited"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 that multiplying a 
\begin_inset Formula $2\times2$
\end_inset

 matrix by scalar 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 multiplies its determinant by 
\begin_inset Formula $c^{2}$
\end_inset

.
 Finally, combined with the facts that the determinants of reflections and
 rotations are 
\begin_inset Formula $-1$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $1$
\end_inset

 respectively, the determinant of any matrix of a similitude is 
\begin_inset Formula $s^{2}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $s$
\end_inset

 is its scale factor.
 Applying this information to equation (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:reptile-area"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

), we get
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
s_{1}^{2}\text{area}(R)+s_{2}^{2}\text{area}(R)+\cdots+s_{p}^{2}\text{area}(R)=\text{area}(R)
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{k}$
\end_inset

 is the scale factor of similitude 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{k}$
\end_inset

.
 Hence
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
s_{1}^{2}+s_{2}^{2}+\cdots+s_{p}^{2}=1.\label{eq:reptile-scale-factors}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


